  MEMEDIT address

Low Memory

This external command lets you edit
contents of memory. Use it only if
you know exactly what you are doing.
It is possible to corrupt the system
or even cause a complete lock-up.

It displays the position, the old
value, and allows you to enter a new
hex value, or press <RETURN> to leave
it unchanged. Press <ESC> to exit the
command.

Address and all values must be entered
as hexadecimal numbers.
